			<tr>
				<td><font face="verdana" size="1">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="/quests/default.asp">Quests</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="default.asp?land=121218">West Cabilis</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline3.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<b>Necro Hammer Quest?</b><br><br>
				</td>
			</tr>
				
			<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Necro Hammer Quest?</b>&nbsp;<a href="../Subscribe.asp?DID=433345"><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><a href="mailto:treatsmiester@aol.com">Celestial Pandemonium</a> | 
		                        5/18/2001 5:33:24 PM</b></font></p>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">You can get a quest from one of the Nihilists standing outside of the Iksar Necro tower in West Cabilis by talking to him some. He'll end up giving you a book, which you must give to The Toilmaster (usually found tending the Froglok Slaves in East Cabilis). In return the Toilmaster will give you a different book - which you must read, for it contains the information you need to do this quest. You must ask the Toilmaster for the Hammer of Exoneration(sp?) and a bag. You also must ask the mortician for a mortar and pestle. Go to some newbie area (I went to the Field of Bone) and keep killing monsters. Make sure you have the hammer equiped - it is a 2 handed blunt weapon, 4 DMG and 60 Delay. The purpose of it (role-playing wise) is to learn patience and such (and you'll notice that you'll run out of stamina while attacking monsters and it will decrese your STR, DEX, and AGI). Now, while you are attacking creatures, the hammer will proc and create NO DROP Bone Fragments (by the way, I believe that all of the items in this quest are NO DROP). You'll need to fill up your mortar and pestle with 8 of these fragments and push the combine button. This will create a powder (bone powder, I believe). You will need 7 of these powders, so you will actually have to get 56 bone fragments (it doesn't take that long). Put the powders in the bag you got from the Toilmaster, ALONG WITH 1 blood water. Combine them, and you'll get a new item. Now, take the book and the bag to the Nihilist who gave you the quest. Now the rest is up to you guys:  when I gave the book and tome to him, he took them and it said he gave me the item that I have been thinking of. I believe the whole point of this quest is to get your newbie robe. I thought the newbie items were supposed to have an * by their names. I didn't look at my robe before I gave him the book and bag, so I am not sure what the name of it or what the AC was - but IF infact he does give you a new robe, it is the &quot;Drape of the Brood&quot;, magic item, no drop, lore item, 4 AC. You also get to keep the hammer and mortar and pestle. Right after I did this quest, I went to the Master that stands in front of the bloody pool (which is just a few steps away from the Nihilist). When you first hail him your first keywords are &quot;new components.&quot; So I asked him... &quot;What new components?&quot; The Master responded as usual, but the Nihilist also said something. The way it sounded, it sounds as if when you give the Nihilist the bag and book, you're supposed to say something to him - perhaps what item you are wanting. I have no clue as to what you could say to him. Perhaps the quest just ends when you give him the book and bag. I don't know... So the rest is up to you all. Good luck!
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
			</tr>
